                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-top:30px"><b> Serene Environment for Healing & Learning</b></li>
                    Nairobi offers a unique balance between urban convenience and natural tranquility. With its lush green spaces, including Karura Forest and the Nairobi Arboretum, the city provides an ideal setting for medical professionals to engage in meaningful discussions on burn care while experiencing a peaceful and restorative atmosphere.

                        <li style="margin-top:30px"><b>World-Class Medical Facilities</b></li>
                        Nairobi is home to leading hospitals and medical research centers specializing in trauma and burn treatment, including Kenyatta National Hospital and Aga Khan University Hospital. Hosting the conference in Nairobi allows participants to connect with top African experts and witness firsthand the advancements in burn treatment across the region.

                        <li style="margin-top:30px"><b>Strategic Location & Connectivity</b></li>
                    As East Africa’s hub, Nairobi is easily accessible from major African cities and beyond, making it convenient for international delegates to attend. Jomo Kenyatta International Airport provides direct flights from various global locations, ensuring smooth travel for participants.

                        <li style="margin-top:30px"><b>Advancing Burn Care in Africa</b></li>
                    Nairobi’s growing focus on emergency and trauma care aligns with the Pan African Burn Society’s mission. By hosting the conference here, the society can strengthen regional collaborations, promote innovative treatments, and advocate for improved burn care policies across the continent.

